  "text": "The single image based depth estimation method in [CITATION_1] employs two deep networks viz. coarse and fine. Whilst the former predicts the global depth of the scene, the latter refines it locally. The output of coarse network also works as supplementary first-layer input of image features to the fine network. The authors exploit a scale-invariant error in measuring the depth relations instead of scale. The reported results after application to NYU Depth and KITTI datasets are better than the state of the art methods but do not establish the need to use the fine network as its contribution to the final results needs a cost/benefit analysis.",
